               <msContents>
                  <summary>Three Miracles of Mary, ተአምረ፡ ማርያም፡; Prayer to Mary, “I take refuge,” ተማኅፀንኩ፡; Hymn to Mary, “In Heaven and on Earth,” በሰማይ፡ ወበምድር፡; Image of the Passion of the Cross, መልክአ፡ ሕማማት፡; Hymn to Sebastian, መልክአ፡ ስብስትያኖስ፡; Image of the Savior of the World, መልክአ፡ መድኃኔ፡ ዓለም፡; Image of Mary Qwəsqwam, መልክአ፡ ቍስቋም፡; Excerpt of the Image of Mary of Edom, መልክአ፡ ኤዶም፡; Hymn to Jesus Christ</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gə‘əz</textLang>

                      <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from = "1r" to = "9v"/>
                     <note>Three Miracles of Mary</note>
                  <title type = "complete" ref = "LIT2384Taamme"/>
                      <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                        <locus from="1r" to="3r"/>
                        <title>How the Virgin Mary spoke from her picture to a
                        devout worshipper and said to him, “Blessed art thou among
                        men”</title>
                        <note>(Budge, II; Princeton 20, ff. 41v–42r; Princeton 23, ff.
                        28v–29v; Princeton 41, ff. 54v; Princeton 43, ff. 8rv; Princeton
                        46, ff. 10v–11r; MYS 1, f. 171v)</note>
                      </msItem>
                      <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                        <locus from="3v" to="6v"/>
                      <title>How an aged Jew of Akhmim, who had spent his
                        whole life in ministering in a church of the Virgin Mary, fell
                        down one day during the service and broke his back, and how
                        the Virgin Mary touched his backbone and made it whole, and
                        made him to stand by her on the right-hand side of the altar</title>
                        <note>(Budge, III; MYS 1, ff. 6v–7r)</note>
                      <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.3">
                        <locus from="6v" to="9v"/>
                      <title>How the scribe Damianus used to write the name of
                        the Virgin Mary in gold and colored paints, and how the Virgin
                        appeared to him when dying, and took his soul to Paradise and
                        showed him his name inscribed upon a pillar of gold</title>
                        <note>(Budge, IV; Princeton Ethiopic 41, ff. 55v–56r; MYS 1, ff. 7rv).</note>
                    </msItem>
               <msItem xml:id="ms_i2"><locus from = "10r" to = "24v"/>
                        <title>Prayer to Mary, “I take refuge.”</title>
                        <incipit xml:lang = "gez">
                          በኵሉ፡ ሕማሙ፡ ዘዕለተ፡ ዓርብ፡ ለፍቁር፡ ወልድኪ፡ ተማኅፀንኩ፡ ኦ፡ እግዝእትየ፡ ማርያም፡ በእኅዞቱ፡ በመጣብሕ፡...
                        </incipit>
                    </msItem>
                      <msItem xml:id="ms_i3"><locus from = "24v" to = "28r"/>
                      <title type = "complete" ref = "LIT2967RepCh248"/>
                        <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                          በሰማይ፡ ወበምድር፡ አልብየ፡ ባዕደ፡...
                        </incipit>
                    </msItem>
                      <msItem xml:id="ms_i4"><locus from = "28r" to = "51v"/>
                      <title type = "complete" ref = "LIT2807RepCh91"/>
                      <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                      ‎ሰላም፡ ለኪ፡ ማርያም፡ ድንግል፡ ዘመዓዛ፡ አፉኪ፡ ኮል፡ ‎
                      ‎እንተ፡ ትጼንዊ፡ በገዳም፡ ወሐቅል፡ ‎
                      ‎ወልታ፡ ረዲኦትየ፡ በውስተ፡ ቀትል፡ ‎
                      </incipit>
                    </msItem>
                      <msItem xml:id="ms_i5"><locus from = "51v" to = "60r"/>
                        <title>Hymn to Sebastian</title>
                        <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                          እንዘ፡ እፈቅድ፡ ፈቂደ፡ ወትሜነይ፡ ተምኔተ።...ሰላም፡ ለኆኅያተ፡ ስምከ፡ በኍልቈ፡ ሰማያት፡ ሰብኡ።...
                        </incipit>
                        <note>Could be any of Chaîne 55, 168, 355</note>
                      </msItem>
                      <msItem xml:id="ms_i6"><locus from = "60v" to = "74v"/>
                        <title type = "complete" ref = "LIT2883RepCh164"/>
                        <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                          ‎ሰላም: ለዝክረ: ስምከ: ዘኢረከቡ: ተፍጻሜተ:‎ መላእክተ: ሰማይ: ወምድር: እለ: ለመዱ: ስብሐተ።...‎
                        </incipit>
                      </msItem>
                      <msItem xml:id="ms_i7"><locus from = "74v" to = "82v"/>
                        <title type = "complete" ref = "LIT1862Malkea"/>
                        <note>This is a form of the text different than Chaîne Répertoire 175</note>
                        <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                          ‎በስመ: እግዚአብሔር: ቀዳማዊ: እንተ: ኢይብልዎ: ማእዜ።‎
                          ‎ወደኃራዊ: ለሊሁ: ዘኢያወሥእዎ: እስከ: ይእዜ።‎
                          ‎ከመ: እጽሐፍ: ለኪ: ማርያም: ተዝካረ: ግፍዕኪ: ባሕረ: ተከዜ።‎
                          ‎ቊስቋም: ትተረጐም: ለርእስየ: በከናፍሪሃ: ኑዛዜ።‎
                          ‎እስመ: ነበረት: ምስሌኪ: በውእቱ: ጊዜ።‎
                        </incipit>
                      </msItem>
                      <msItem xml:id="ms_i8"><locus target = "#82v"/>
                        <note>First few lines only</note>
                        <title type = "complete" ref = "LIT2940RepCh221"/>
                      </msItem>
                      <msItem xml:id="ms_i9"><locus from = "82r" to = "82v"/>
                      <title>Hymn to Jesus Christ</title>
                      <note>incomplete at the beginning</note>
                    </msItem>


                      </msItem>
